1
00:00:55,500 --> 00:01:00,062
When people finish their day
and hurry home,

2
00:01:00,594 --> 00:01:02,219
my day starts.

3
00:01:19,666 --> 00:01:23,875
My diner is open from midnight
to 7:00 in the morning.

4
00:01:24,531 --> 00:01:27,948
They call it "Midnight Diner."

5
00:01:33,392 --> 00:01:35,399
Do I even have customers?

6
00:01:35,399 --> 00:01:37,732
More than you would expect.

7
00:01:39,740 --> 00:01:41,717
MIDNIGHT DINER: TOKYO STORIES

8
00:01:41,717 --> 00:01:47,390
CRAB AND TOSHIKOSHI SOBA

9
00:02:05,531 --> 00:02:06,948
Just kidding!

10
00:02:08,111 --> 00:02:11,361
Look! It's a doggy mailman!

11
00:02:22,151 --> 00:02:23,151
Let go!

12
00:02:23,492 --> 00:02:24,992
-Let go!
-Ouch!

13
00:02:57,825 --> 00:02:59,491
Just what I needed!

14
00:03:01,069 --> 00:03:04,319
Thanks for stopping me,
I almost lost a lot of money.

15
00:03:04,908 --> 00:03:08,667
You won't last in this job if you
get mad at something like that.

16
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:14,098
But I much prefer the mascot uniform.
It's better than doing weird cosplay.

17
00:03:14,471 --> 00:03:15,804
Is the pay different?

18
00:03:16,853 --> 00:03:19,103
Cosplay is 100 yen more.

19
00:03:19,741 --> 00:03:20,783
A little while back,

20
00:03:21,408 --> 00:03:24,432
I was a cheerleader at a
home supplies shop in Ibaraki.

21
00:03:24,432 --> 00:03:26,601
-For real?
-It was under the table.

22
00:03:26,950 --> 00:03:29,783
The train fare alone was 2,000 yen.

23
00:03:29,783 --> 00:03:31,282
That's like a day trip!

24
00:03:33,314 --> 00:03:35,633
How much is this ramen, again? 10 yen?

25
00:03:35,755 --> 00:03:38,671
No, it's 750 yen. Including tax.

26
00:03:38,943 --> 00:03:40,193
Really?

27
00:03:42,477 --> 00:03:43,810
What's your name?

28
00:03:44,339 --> 00:03:46,755
-Noriko.
-Nori-chan.

29
00:03:47,485 --> 00:03:48,485
I'm Gen.

30
00:03:49,606 --> 00:03:51,065
I'll treat you tonight.

31
00:03:52,525 --> 00:03:54,275
-Are you sure?
-Of course.

32
00:03:55,118 --> 00:03:56,012
-Really?
-Yeah.

33
00:04:38,113 --> 00:04:41,280
I haven't seen a
coffin-shaped piggy bank in ages.

34
00:04:41,979 --> 00:04:43,979
It's for my winnings at the horse track.

35
00:04:44,700 --> 00:04:46,783
It sure is hard to save money.

36
00:04:47,605 --> 00:04:49,986
Your part-time job is rough, right?

37
00:04:50,615 --> 00:04:54,323
It's a job where you don't need
to prove your identity, right?

38
00:04:55,325 --> 00:04:57,450
It must be a rough group you work with.

39
00:04:58,158 --> 00:05:00,481
But not the girl you're talking about?

40
00:05:00,481 --> 00:05:03,756
Yeah... she's super hard-working,

41
00:05:03,756 --> 00:05:06,813
almost as if this job is
the only thing she's got.

42
00:05:13,163 --> 00:05:15,186
You make gratin so rarely!

43
00:05:15,602 --> 00:05:18,940
There was a sale on macaroni today.

44
00:05:19,283 --> 00:05:20,283
Try it.

45
00:05:25,086 --> 00:05:26,170
It's delicious!

46
00:05:27,139 --> 00:05:30,347
-It's warming me up!
-Hot!

47
00:05:32,439 --> 00:05:33,439
By the way, Master,

48
00:05:34,027 --> 00:05:35,252
how's this year's crab?

49
00:05:36,483 --> 00:05:37,733
It should be soon.

50
00:05:38,543 --> 00:05:41,669
My friend... is getting me some good ones.

51
00:05:42,434 --> 00:05:44,323
I'm so excited!

52
00:05:44,999 --> 00:05:46,291
I've got an idea, Gen.

53
00:05:46,727 --> 00:05:48,352
Why don't you bring her here?

54
00:05:48,711 --> 00:05:51,345
I'm sure she'd love to try Master's food.

55
00:05:53,075 --> 00:05:54,194
That's true.

56
00:05:59,341 --> 00:06:00,216
Yes!

57
00:06:00,854 --> 00:06:04,521
This tempura is much better than
the ones you can find out there.

58
00:06:05,223 --> 00:06:08,624
Do you have any more of these?

59
00:06:08,624 --> 00:06:11,224
I gave them all away.
I'll bring some next time.

60
00:06:11,224 --> 00:06:13,739
Here you go, fried udon.

61
00:06:20,685 --> 00:06:23,419
When did I turn into a son-in-law?

62
00:06:24,953 --> 00:06:26,044
What do you mean?

63
00:06:27,066 --> 00:06:31,760
I showed Saori how to make soba,
and my mom said hers was better than mine.

64
00:06:33,418 --> 00:06:34,601
Is it that different?

65
00:06:34,927 --> 00:06:38,362
No, I think it's just a matter of taste.

66
00:06:39,025 --> 00:06:43,816
But, in fact, some customers have asked
for Saori's soba instead of mine.

67
00:06:45,733 --> 00:06:48,317
Our deliveries have even gone up.

68
00:06:48,317 --> 00:06:49,650
Why's she so popular?

69
00:06:50,941 --> 00:06:53,187
Your mother's happy about it, right?

70
00:06:53,187 --> 00:06:55,873
She's calling Saori her "next-in-line."

71
00:06:58,564 --> 00:07:00,212
You've been replaced!

72
00:07:00,706 --> 00:07:04,597
I'm supposed to take over the business,
but now I've lost my motivation.

73
00:07:06,161 --> 00:07:07,494
Thanks for the food.

74
00:07:25,138 --> 00:07:26,679
Thank you for today.

75
00:07:27,478 --> 00:07:30,353
Let's get something to eat.
That place over there is good.

76
00:07:31,900 --> 00:07:34,233
What... That one?

77
00:07:35,254 --> 00:07:36,671
-You know it?
-No...

78
00:07:37,241 --> 00:07:38,199
I don't...

79
00:07:38,966 --> 00:07:40,716
Let's go, then. My treat.

80
00:07:44,348 --> 00:07:45,408
Aren't you hungry?

81
00:07:45,408 --> 00:07:46,188
I am.

82
00:07:46,188 --> 00:07:47,215
You are?

83
00:07:47,620 --> 00:07:48,662
Then let's go.

84
00:07:57,941 --> 00:07:58,775
Are you cold?

85
00:07:59,764 --> 00:08:02,264
No, I think I caught a cold.

86
00:08:02,980 --> 00:08:04,605
Here you go.

87
00:08:08,958 --> 00:08:12,929
Master, this is the girl
I was telling you about.

88
00:08:12,929 --> 00:08:13,909
Nori-chan.

89
00:08:16,983 --> 00:08:18,150
Cheers.

90
00:08:18,779 --> 00:08:19,612
Cheers.

91
00:08:22,678 --> 00:08:24,622
Shall I turn up the heat?

92
00:08:25,466 --> 00:08:26,966
No, I'm fine.

93
00:08:27,730 --> 00:08:30,605
Order what you like.
He can make almost anything.

94
00:08:32,236 --> 00:08:33,403
What do you want?

95
00:08:34,713 --> 00:08:37,223
-I'll have...
-Stewed meat and potatoes, right?

96
00:08:46,716 --> 00:08:47,978
It's been a while.

97
00:08:52,709 --> 00:08:53,584
What?

98
00:08:54,165 --> 00:08:55,623
-What is it?
-A few years ago,

99
00:08:56,025 --> 00:09:00,691
this girl was involved in a marriage scam
with her older sister.

100
00:09:01,319 --> 00:09:04,712
One of my customers fell victim to them.

101
00:09:09,292 --> 00:09:11,350
I served a three-year sentence.

102
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:14,824
I meant to come sooner, but...

103
00:09:17,036 --> 00:09:18,203
And your sister?

104
00:09:18,816 --> 00:09:21,774
After getting out of jail,
she went back to Hokkaido.

105
00:09:23,946 --> 00:09:27,029
I never imagined it was you
Gen was talking about.

106
00:09:27,736 --> 00:09:31,864
Try my stewed meat and potatoes.
You haven't had it for a while.

107
00:09:34,207 --> 00:09:35,374
Thank you.

108
00:09:46,141 --> 00:09:47,183
Wow...

109
00:09:48,433 --> 00:09:50,016
It hasn't changed at all.

110
00:09:51,891 --> 00:09:53,100
This is it!

111
00:09:56,282 --> 00:10:00,111
You've served your time,
so you don't need to be embarrassed.

112
00:10:02,337 --> 00:10:03,754
Do you have any other work?

113
00:10:09,933 --> 00:10:11,539
I tried everywhere,

114
00:10:12,361 --> 00:10:15,871
but the three-year gap
in my résumé is hard to explain.

115
00:10:15,871 --> 00:10:17,579
Write whatever, then.

116
00:10:18,475 --> 00:10:19,933
I don't want to lie anymore.

117
00:10:21,356 --> 00:10:24,731
I've already hurt enough people.

118
00:10:31,012 --> 00:10:33,277
Master, shochu and oolong tea, please.

119
00:10:33,959 --> 00:10:34,876
Sure.

120
00:10:43,354 --> 00:10:44,479
Ready?

121
00:10:56,673 --> 00:10:59,798
The key is snapping.
You have to tense up your wrist.

122
00:11:04,624 --> 00:11:06,082
Shall we try farther away?

123
00:11:07,766 --> 00:11:10,808
Excuse me. Sorry.

124
00:11:13,641 --> 00:11:14,641
Ready?

125
00:11:27,633 --> 00:11:31,133
Don't give me that.
Why are you skipping work?

126
00:11:31,524 --> 00:11:33,193
I wanted some fried udon.

127
00:11:33,625 --> 00:11:34,653
Are you busy?

128
00:11:34,993 --> 00:11:36,566
Isn't that obvious?

129
00:11:38,497 --> 00:11:42,532
You and my mom will
do just fine without me.

130
00:11:42,532 --> 00:11:44,907
What? Are you pouting?

131
00:11:47,414 --> 00:11:50,369
Maybe it would've been better
if we didn't get together.

132
00:11:52,091 --> 00:11:53,574
Excuse me.

133
00:11:58,636 --> 00:12:00,470
What a child!

134
00:12:10,001 --> 00:12:14,437
It's Christmas Eve, and all customers
who purchase a cake worth over 2,000 yen

135
00:12:14,437 --> 00:12:17,166
will be given a free macaron
of your choice!

136
00:12:18,580 --> 00:12:20,089
Did you buy your cake?

137
00:12:20,089 --> 00:12:21,529
Thank you very much!

138
00:12:32,753 --> 00:12:34,045
We should get going.

139
00:12:34,783 --> 00:12:36,450
-Good night.
-Good night.

140
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:41,593
Excuse me!

141
00:12:42,214 --> 00:12:43,214
Yes?

142
00:12:44,091 --> 00:12:45,591
Nice to meet you.

143
00:12:46,358 --> 00:12:50,431
I have good news and bad news.
Which would you like to hear first?

144
00:12:50,718 --> 00:12:51,724
Neither.

145
00:12:52,191 --> 00:12:54,524
The bad news is you caught my eye.

146
00:12:55,133 --> 00:12:56,351
That was unlucky.

147
00:12:56,661 --> 00:13:00,953
But the good news will make you
forget all about that.

148
00:13:01,300 --> 00:13:04,312
I saw the way you were working.

149
00:13:05,436 --> 00:13:09,281
In a world where most people
are cruel and unthoughtful,

150
00:13:09,281 --> 00:13:11,823
I see a golden halo...

151
00:13:12,842 --> 00:13:15,050
glowing around your head.

152
00:13:16,157 --> 00:13:17,657
Do you want to be a model?

153
00:13:18,637 --> 00:13:22,014
I'm absolutely sure that
you would be a success.

154
00:13:22,550 --> 00:13:26,514
Do you really think I would
fall for something like--

155
00:13:26,514 --> 00:13:27,931
Let me give you...

156
00:13:30,441 --> 00:13:31,305
your contract fee.

157
00:13:50,637 --> 00:13:52,039
-What are you doing?
-Yes?

158
00:13:56,425 --> 00:13:57,758
-Who are you?
-I'm...

159
00:13:59,050 --> 00:14:00,175
What's this?

160
00:14:02,758 --> 00:14:05,803
Ouch! Ouch! Ouch!

161
00:14:05,803 --> 00:14:07,243
Stop it!

162
00:14:07,590 --> 00:14:09,132
What are you doing?

163
00:14:09,841 --> 00:14:11,258
Let's go, Nori-chan.

164
00:14:11,998 --> 00:14:12,914
Hey!

165
00:14:17,659 --> 00:14:20,733
Don't touch it! Go away!

166
00:14:22,936 --> 00:14:25,457
I knew it was a scam, but...

167
00:14:27,262 --> 00:14:30,012
when I saw the money
I couldn't control myself.

168
00:14:33,420 --> 00:14:34,629
I'm so embarrassed.

169
00:14:42,527 --> 00:14:44,254
I have a record, too.

170
00:14:49,246 --> 00:14:50,579
I've served time.

171
00:14:56,613 --> 00:14:59,764
We need to take care of ourselves, right?

172
00:15:03,591 --> 00:15:04,675
Yes.

173
00:15:11,550 --> 00:15:13,328
It's a little early, but...

174
00:15:13,773 --> 00:15:15,421
here's a Christmas present.

175
00:15:15,809 --> 00:15:16,655
For both of you.

176
00:15:19,947 --> 00:15:21,156
Are you sure?

177
00:15:23,362 --> 00:15:25,821
By "present," you mean it's free, right?

178
00:15:28,091 --> 00:15:30,301
Let me know if you want more.
There are lots.

179
00:15:30,301 --> 00:15:32,295
Let's dig in, then!

180
00:15:32,295 --> 00:15:33,503
Thank you!

181
00:15:37,754 --> 00:15:38,587
Delicious.

182
00:15:40,062 --> 00:15:41,437
What's this?

183
00:15:42,514 --> 00:15:43,973
This is the real deal!

184
00:15:45,208 --> 00:15:46,541
Master, it's amazing!

185
00:15:48,083 --> 00:15:49,693
This is free, right?

186
00:15:49,693 --> 00:15:51,984
Welcome, welcome!

187
00:15:51,984 --> 00:15:56,482
Japanese! Japanese!
Traditional goods. Very lucky.

188
00:15:57,286 --> 00:15:59,602
You can choose anything you like.

189
00:15:59,602 --> 00:16:01,810
They're great for souvenirs!

190
00:16:02,916 --> 00:16:06,114
-Must buy. Must buy.
-Must buy.

191
00:16:06,114 --> 00:16:07,928
Thank you very much!

192
00:16:07,928 --> 00:16:09,723
-Happy New Year!
-How much?

193
00:16:17,814 --> 00:16:19,166
What's it called again?

194
00:16:19,613 --> 00:16:22,102
That scam where men
show off a bunch of money...

195
00:16:22,402 --> 00:16:24,652
to fool women into selling themselves?

196
00:16:25,268 --> 00:16:25,941
The soul-snatching scam.

197
00:16:25,941 --> 00:16:27,894
SOUL-SNATCHING SCAM = SOUL SCAM
The soul-snatching scam.

198
00:16:27,894 --> 00:16:30,654
SOUL-SNATCHING SCAM = SOUL SCAM
That's where that other scam was busted two years ago.

199
00:16:30,654 --> 00:16:33,068
That's where that other scam was busted two years ago.

200
00:16:33,795 --> 00:16:36,795
You think scam artists
always use the same locations?

201
00:16:37,812 --> 00:16:41,687
People like that think
they're smarter than us.

202
00:16:42,726 --> 00:16:44,268
That's been my experience.

203
00:17:10,083 --> 00:17:11,125
Good evening.

204
00:17:13,238 --> 00:17:15,738
Sorry to call you at such a busy time.

205
00:17:16,916 --> 00:17:20,583
You'll need help if you want to make
even more soba than last year.

206
00:17:21,416 --> 00:17:25,333
Usually I'm given some,
but I didn't get any this year.

207
00:17:26,416 --> 00:17:28,541
I want to make sure I have enough.

208
00:17:38,819 --> 00:17:40,444
I'm hungry...

209
00:17:41,866 --> 00:17:45,950
Saori made the soba today.

210
00:17:47,424 --> 00:17:48,810
"Proprietress-to-be of Sobasei."

211
00:17:48,810 --> 00:17:50,690
I'm getting excited.

212
00:17:51,081 --> 00:17:53,748
Soba tastes different
depending on how it's made.

213
00:17:54,828 --> 00:17:58,784
Master, can you make
this year's New Year's soba with tempura?

214
00:17:59,529 --> 00:18:02,083
Tempura was shop-bought,
if you don't mind.

215
00:18:03,294 --> 00:18:05,752
Aren't you avoiding fried foods?

216
00:18:06,482 --> 00:18:09,263
I'm going to at least treat myself
at the end of the year.

217
00:18:09,688 --> 00:18:11,456
They just go so well together!

218
00:18:13,025 --> 00:18:15,217
It's about time to boil the noodles...

219
00:18:27,545 --> 00:18:28,682
Master!

220
00:18:28,795 --> 00:18:29,935
What is it?

221
00:18:30,545 --> 00:18:33,817
We had extra shrimp,
so I brought them to make tempura.

222
00:18:35,046 --> 00:18:38,116
Thanks, but it's difficult to do it here.

223
00:18:38,116 --> 00:18:40,483
Master, two hot sakes, please.

224
00:18:41,240 --> 00:18:42,128
Sure!

225
00:19:02,860 --> 00:19:04,902
The aroma of soba is wonderful.

226
00:19:05,713 --> 00:19:07,634
The tempura is delicious, too!

227
00:19:08,134 --> 00:19:11,221
Master did cook it himself.

228
00:19:11,221 --> 00:19:13,481
-He's too good!
-Right?

229
00:19:21,325 --> 00:19:22,825
You can't beat the tempura...

230
00:19:23,399 --> 00:19:25,066
from a soba shop.

231
00:19:26,246 --> 00:19:27,704
Is this from a soba shop?

232
00:19:33,917 --> 00:19:36,036
This is amazing!

233
00:19:37,216 --> 00:19:39,883
We need two more servings.

234
00:19:39,883 --> 00:19:40,925
Sure.

235
00:20:03,832 --> 00:20:06,909
Master said those were for us.

236
00:20:17,215 --> 00:20:18,424
Good work.

237
00:20:19,533 --> 00:20:21,651
Thanks. You, too.

238
00:20:23,408 --> 00:20:26,075
It doesn't taste like real Sobasei
if one of us is missing.

239
00:20:48,858 --> 00:20:50,066
Thank you.

240
00:21:03,910 --> 00:21:05,451
Move along, please.

241
00:21:05,451 --> 00:21:06,909
Don't stop. Keep going.

242
00:21:06,909 --> 00:21:08,219
Careful, please.

243
00:21:08,219 --> 00:21:10,970
If you stand still,
you might loose things in life.

244
00:21:10,970 --> 00:21:12,928
What happened, Kogure?

245
00:21:13,450 --> 00:21:14,863
I'm sorry for the bother.

246
00:21:14,863 --> 00:21:17,741
I'll tell you later when
I stop by for some soba.

247
00:21:18,667 --> 00:21:21,458
Step back, please. Don't line up.

248
00:21:21,458 --> 00:21:25,239
Save the lining up for when you make
offerings at the shrine tomorrow.

249
00:21:25,611 --> 00:21:27,403
It sounds like the police.

250
00:21:28,904 --> 00:21:30,437
It's cold. Let's go back.

251
00:21:33,075 --> 00:21:34,741
That's an unlucky spot.

252
00:21:35,863 --> 00:21:38,779
The New Year is coming,
you should all go home.

253
00:21:40,648 --> 00:21:41,843
Nothing to see here.

254
00:21:47,900 --> 00:21:49,409
The guy with wads of cash!

255
00:21:50,862 --> 00:21:53,244
I'm glad they got him before the New Year.

256
00:21:54,327 --> 00:21:56,514
Let's leave this year's sins behind.

257
00:22:08,829 --> 00:22:10,579
It's the New Year.

258
00:22:11,704 --> 00:22:12,436
But...

259
00:22:12,860 --> 00:22:17,591
they say you mix the year's bad luck
into the soba and eat it to get rid of it.

260
00:22:17,591 --> 00:22:20,341
So, isn't it bad
we didn't finish it in time?

261
00:22:20,341 --> 00:22:23,202
I don't think it's a problem.

262
00:22:23,863 --> 00:22:26,140
Think of it like,
"Last year's bad luck is over,

263
00:22:26,140 --> 00:22:28,100
and we'll do better this year."

264
00:22:33,691 --> 00:22:36,648
I was really impressed with your work.

265
00:22:38,535 --> 00:22:41,457
Thank you for your leadership.

266
00:22:42,363 --> 00:22:43,822
I was just lucky.

267
00:22:44,819 --> 00:22:47,055
Cops' intuitions...

268
00:22:47,561 --> 00:22:50,478
are like human emotions:
you can't rely on them.

269
00:22:54,382 --> 00:22:55,549
You know...

270
00:22:56,316 --> 00:22:58,936
I get the feeling that...

271
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:01,229
this is my last case.

272
00:23:09,816 --> 00:23:11,171
It's snowing!

273
00:23:20,365 --> 00:23:22,021
It's freshly made!

274
00:23:22,021 --> 00:23:24,617
It was difficult to get here.

275
00:23:24,617 --> 00:23:26,325
Who wants to roll it out?

276
00:23:26,325 --> 00:23:27,817
Can I?

277
00:23:28,608 --> 00:23:30,796
-Like this?
-Yes, gently.

278
00:23:35,900 --> 00:23:37,160
You should cut it.

279
00:23:38,140 --> 00:23:38,903
What?

280
00:23:39,296 --> 00:23:41,557
That's your job.

281
00:23:41,557 --> 00:23:44,458
I'm here to grill it, not to cut it.

282
00:23:51,108 --> 00:23:51,941
What is it?

283
00:24:00,772 --> 00:24:01,897
Delicious.

284
00:24:18,191 --> 00:24:19,634
It's so good!

285
00:24:20,542 --> 00:24:22,167
-It's delicious.
-Here you go.

286
00:24:24,830 --> 00:24:29,484
When people finish their day
and hurry home,

287
00:24:29,484 --> 00:24:31,317
my day starts.

288
00:24:35,025 --> 00:24:39,226
My diner is open from midnight
to 7:00 in the morning.

289
00:24:39,834 --> 00:24:43,128
They call it "Midnight Diner."

290
00:24:45,877 --> 00:24:47,360
Do I even have customers?

291
00:24:47,735 --> 00:24:50,360
More than you would expect.

